The paper proposes an efficient local search algorithm for the partial Latin square extension problem, which is a combinatorial optimization problem. This problem is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of local search and iterated local search also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the complexity of the problem, which could be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the comparison with state-of-the-art optimization solvers suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
